The paper deals with string indexing problems with range reporting features, which are typically studied in the data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The use of suffix trees and range reporting data structures suggests a focus on computational geometry (cs.CG) and algorithms and complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper's emphasis on time-space trade-offs and reductions suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
